WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.361 --> 00:00:03.030
(strong music)

00:00:03.030 --> 00:00:06.390
- Once I began to understand
protein requirements

00:00:06.390 --> 00:00:10.290
for muscle protein synthesis,
for building muscle,

00:00:10.290 --> 00:00:12.910
I quickly realized that
we need a lot more protein

00:00:12.910 --> 00:00:14.290
than most people are getting.

00:00:14.290 --> 00:00:17.710
It's basically a gram
per pound of body weight.

00:00:17.710 --> 00:00:20.450
Steak, for example, is 38% usable.

00:00:20.450 --> 00:00:24.190
Whey protein is 18% usable,

00:00:24.190 --> 00:00:27.100
so most of whey protein you're taking in

00:00:27.100 --> 00:00:29.000
is not usable by the body.

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:31.700
When I created Fortagen,

00:00:31.700 --> 00:00:34.476
the objective was the
most efficient protein.

00:00:34.476 --> 00:00:37.750
It's 100% essential amino acids.

00:00:37.750 --> 00:00:41.240
It's base was from a cancer treatment,

00:00:41.240 --> 00:00:43.040
so it was the most efficient protein,

00:00:43.040 --> 00:00:45.950
the smallest amount of
material to be digested

00:00:45.950 --> 00:00:50.060
to have the highest protein
value for cellular repair.

00:00:50.060 --> 00:00:53.710
All we did was we took
that cancer treatment

00:00:53.710 --> 00:00:56.550
and then adjusted some of the ratios

00:00:56.550 --> 00:01:00.220
so that instead of looking
at repair of damaged cells

00:01:00.220 --> 00:01:02.640
from chemotherapy and radiation,

00:01:02.640 --> 00:01:05.010
what we're doing is giving the body

00:01:05.010 --> 00:01:07.630
what it needs for the maximum amount

00:01:07.630 --> 00:01:09.440
of muscle protein synthesis.

00:01:09.440 --> 00:01:11.790
It's very efficient

00:01:11.790 --> 00:01:15.593
and will drive you towards
your muscle building goal.

